The second one is the fwdshift function, which works in the opposite way to the lag1 function: It shifts the time series one step forward.

function y=fwdshift(day,x)
assert(day>=0);

y=[x(day+1:end,:,:); ..
NaN*ones(day,size(x,2), size(x, 3))];
